        "content": "<p>Is there code for an inner product space that’s also an algebra, but not necessarily that <code>‖x * y‖ ≤ ‖x‖ * ‖y‖</code>?<br>\nSo <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=NormedRing#doc\">docs#NormedRing</a> but without the <code>norm_mul_le</code> property?</p>",
        "id": 529892622,
        "sender_full_name": "Monica Omar",
        "timestamp": 1753104914
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>No, and I think probably the plan is to achieve this via changing the spelling of <code>[NormedRing R]</code> to <code>[Ring R] [NormedRing R]</code></p>",
        "id": 529894891,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1753105584
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>With that change, what you want would be <code>[Ring R] [NormedAddCommGroup R]</code></p>",
